const UserTrackElementsList& GetUserTrackRequest::getResult (   ) 
 

Get a reference to a list with the elements in the reply.

Might contain 0 elements if no track points are registered in the requested interval. Use getStatus to get the status of the request!

The returned list (refernce) is valid until this request is deleted.

Returns:
A list with the elements in the requested interval.

void GetUserTrackRequest::setTimeInterval (  uint32  startTime,
uint32  endTime = MAX_UINT32
) 
 

Set time interval.

The start time is the time when the tracking points should start to be extracted. This implies that start time should be less than current time! The optional end time describes the end interval of the track points to extract. If not set, all points from start time will be returned.

Parameters:
startTime The lower part of the time interval.
endTime Optional parameter with the upper part of the time interval. Current time is used if not set.
